arguments.prompt:
You are working in `/tmp/sv-f21ef26b90a54c4d9c1c082c7babf364`, a Blazor Web App (.NET 11) with **per-page Interactive Server** mode. The MainLayout is static (no `@rendermode`). Individual pages like Counter.razor opt in with `@rendermode InteractiveServer`.

The root namespace is `sv_f21ef26b90a54c4d9c1c082c7babf364`.

## Task

Build an app-wide theme system with these files. The key architectural insight is:

- MainLayout is **static SSR** — it renders once per request and cannot react to state changes.
- BUT you can embed **interactive island components** (with `@rendermode InteractiveServer`) inside the static layout. These islands share the same SignalR circuit as interactive pages.
- A **scoped service** in Interactive Server mode is scoped to the circuit (per-user), so all interactive components (layout islands + page components) share the same instance.
- The service uses a C# event to notify all subscribers when theme changes, so every interactive component updates immediately.
- JS interop persists the theme to `localStorage` so it survives enhanced navigation.

## Files to create

### 1. `Components/Services/ThemeService.cs`

```csharp
namespace sv_f21ef26b90a54c4d9c1c082c7babf364.Components.Services;

public enum ThemeMode
{
    Light,
    Dark,
    System
}

public sealed class ThemeService
{
    private ThemeMode _theme = ThemeMode.System;
    private string _accentColor = "#0d6efd"; // Bootstrap primary

    public ThemeMode Theme
    {
        get => _theme;
        set
        {
            if (_theme == value) return;
            _theme = value;
            NotifyChanged();
        }
    }

    public string AccentColor
    {
        get => _accentColor;
        set
        {
            if (_accentColor == value) return;
            _accentColor = value;
            NotifyChanged();
        }
    }

    public string CssClass => Theme switch
    {
        ThemeMode.Dark => "theme-dark",
        ThemeMode.Light => "theme-light",
        _ => "theme-system"
    };

    public event Action? OnChange;

    private void NotifyChanged() => OnChange?.Invoke();
}
```

### 2. `Components/Layout/ThemeIndicator.razor`

This is an **interactive island** embedded in the static MainLayout. It subscribes to `ThemeService.OnChange` and re-renders when the theme changes.

```razor
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@implements IDisposable
@inject ThemeService ThemeService

<span class="theme-indicator" style="color: @ThemeService.AccentColor;" title="Current theme">
    @GetThemeIcon() @ThemeService.Theme
</span>

@code {
    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        ThemeService.OnChange += OnThemeChanged;
    }

    private void OnThemeChanged()
    {
        InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged);
    }

    private string GetThemeIcon() => ThemeService.Theme switch
    {
        ThemeMode.Light => "☀️",
        ThemeMode.Dark => "🌙",
        _ => "💻"
    };

    public void Dispose()
    {
        ThemeService.OnChange -= OnThemeChanged;
    }
}
```

### 3. `Components/Layout/ThemeToggle.razor`

A quick toggle button (also an interactive island) that can be placed in the sidebar or header.

```razor
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@implements IDisposable
@inject ThemeService ThemeService

<button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" @onclick="CycleTheme"
        title="Toggle theme">
    @GetThemeIcon()
</button>

@code {
    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        ThemeService.OnChange += OnThemeChanged;
    }

    private void CycleTheme()
    {
        ThemeService.Theme = ThemeService.Theme switch
        {
            ThemeMode.Light => ThemeMode.Dark,
            ThemeMode.Dark => ThemeMode.System,
            _ => ThemeMode.Light
        };
    }

    private void OnThemeChanged()
    {
        InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged);
    }

    private string GetThemeIcon() => ThemeService.Theme switch
    {
        ThemeMode.Light => "☀️",
        ThemeMode.Dark => "🌙",
        _ => "💻"
    };

    public void Dispose()
    {
        ThemeService.OnChange -= OnThemeChanged;
    }
}
```

### 4. `Components/Pages/Settings.razor`

Full settings page where user can change theme and accent color.

```razor
@page "/settings"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@implements IDisposable
@inject ThemeService ThemeService

<PageTitle>Settings</PageTitle>

<h1>User Preferences</h1>

<div class="card p-4" style="max-width: 500px;">
    <h4>Theme</h4>
    <div class="btn-group mb-3" role="group">
        @foreach (var mode in Enum.GetValues<ThemeMode>())
        {
            <button class="btn @(ThemeService.Theme == mode ? "btn-primary" : "btn-outline-primary")"
                    @onclick="() => ThemeService.Theme = mode">
                @mode
            </button>
        }
    </div>

    <h4>Accent Color</h4>
    <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <input type="color" class="form-control form-control-color"
               value="@ThemeService.AccentColor"
               @onchange="OnAccentChanged" />
        <span style="color: @ThemeService.AccentColor; font-weight: bold;">
            @ThemeService.AccentColor
        </span>
    </div>

    <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
        <strong>Current:</strong> @ThemeService.Theme mode,
        accent <span style="color: @ThemeService.AccentColor;">@ThemeService.AccentColor</span>
        <br/>
        <small>Changes apply immediately to all components, including the header indicator.</small>
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        ThemeService.OnChange += OnThemeChanged;
    }

    private void OnAccentChanged(ChangeEventArgs e)
    {
        ThemeService.AccentColor = e.Value?.ToString() ?? "#0d6efd";
    }

    private void OnThemeChanged()
    {
        InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged);
    }

    public void Dispose()
    {
        ThemeService.OnChange -= OnThemeChanged;
    }
}
```

## Files to modify

### 5. `Program.cs` — register the service as **Scoped**

Add `using sv_f21ef26b90a54c4d9c1c082c7babf364.Components.Services;` at the top, and after `AddInteractiveServerComponents()` add:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<ThemeService>();
```

### 6. `Components/_Imports.razor` — add the service namespace

Add this line:
```
@using sv_f21ef26b90a54c4d9c1c082c7babf364.Components.Services
```

### 7. `Components/Layout/MainLayout.razor` — embed the interactive islands

Replace the top-row div to include `ThemeIndicator` and `ThemeToggle`:

```razor
@inherits LayoutComponentBase

<div class="page">
    <div class="sidebar">
        <NavMenu />
    </div>

    <main>
        <div class="top-row px-4">
            <ThemeIndicator />
            <ThemeToggle />
            <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/aspnet/core/" target="_blank">About</a>
        </div>

        <article class="content px-4">
            @Body
        </article>
    </main>
</div>

<div id="blazor-error-ui" data-nosnippet>
    An unhandled error has occurred.
    <a href="." class="reload">Reload</a>
    <span class="dismiss">🗙</span>
</div>
```

### 8. `Components/Layout/NavMenu.razor` — add a Settings link

Read the existing NavMenu.razor and add a nav link for Settings, similar to the existing nav links. Something like:

```razor
<div class="nav-item px-3">
    <NavLink class="nav-link" href="settings">
        <span class="bi bi-gear-fill-nav-menu" aria-hidden="true"></span> Settings
    </NavLink>
</div>
```

## After creating/modifying all files

Run `dotnet build` in the project directory to verify everything compiles. Fix any issues.

## Important notes

- The `ThemeService` MUST be registered as `Scoped`, not `Singleton`. In Interactive Server mode, scoped = per-circuit = per-user. Singleton would share state across all users.
- The `ThemeIndicator` and `ThemeToggle` components MUST have `@rendermode InteractiveServer` so they become interactive islands within the static layout. Without this, they'd be static and unable to react to changes.
- All components that consume `ThemeService` must subscribe to `OnChange` and call `InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged)` — this is required because the event fires from a different component's context.
- All subscribers must implement `IDisposable` and unsubscribe to prevent memory leaks.

